<h1 class="doc-page-title">Data dictionary</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">Complete reference of COMPASS database tables, columns, data types, and constraints.</p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> This data dictionary is automatically generated from the Entity Framework Core model and reflects the current database schema.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="conventions">How to read the data dictionary</h2>
<p>The tables below follow consistent naming conventions and data governance rules. Use this primer before exploring individual entities.</p>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h3 class="h6">Column naming</h3>
                <ul class="small mb-0">
                    <li><strong>Primary keys</strong> use <code>Id</code> and auto-increment integers unless stated.</li>
                    <li><strong>Foreign keys</strong> append <code>Id</code> to the related entity name (for example <code>RiskTierId</code>, <code>ObjectiveId</code>).</li>
                    <li><strong>Audit fields</strong> appear as <code>CreatedAt</code>, <code>UpdatedAt</code>, and <code>IsDeleted</code> for soft deletes where applicable.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h3 class="h6">Data types</h3>
                <ul class="small mb-0">
                    <li><strong>VARCHAR</strong> lengths mirror EF Core annotations. Values remain case sensitive.</li>
                    <li><strong>BOOLEAN</strong> flags are stored as <code>bit</code> in SQL Server and default to false unless stated.</li>
                    <li><strong>DATETIME</strong> values are persisted in UTC. Application services convert to local time zones at display time.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-secondary">
    <p class="mb-0"><strong>Tip:</strong> Soft-deleted rows remain in the database with <code>IsDeleted = 1</code>. API endpoints and UI queries filter them automatically, but analysts can include them when producing historical reports.</p>
</div>

